h3. Issue Summary

Parallel sprints are not available for next-gen projects. However, it's possible to assign an issue from a classic project to a not yet started next-gen sprint. This will cause the not yet started next-gen sprint to appear in a classic scrum board, which will allow this last sprint to be started. Doing this, will cause all items from the backlog of the next-gen project to disappear.
h3. Environment
 * Next-gen projects;
 * Sprints;
 * Boards;

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a next-gen project with some issues;
 # Create a sprint, put some issues in it, and then start this sprint;
 # Create another sprint in the next-gen project and don't put any issues on it;
 # On a classic project, create an issue and assign to the second sprint created in the next-gen project;
 # When the second next-gen sprint appear in the classic board, start the second sprint;
 # Go back to the next-gen project;

h3. Expected Results

The issues on the backlog should be visible.
h3. Actual Results

The issues from the backlog disappear.

A short video containing the steps above is available here: [https://cl.ly/d56b05168534]
h3. Workaround

The quickest way to resolve this is to delete the extra next-gen sprint(s) that have been started:
 # Navigate to a classic project backlog
 # Assign an issue on the backlog to the next-gen sprint you would like to delete
 # Once the sprint appears on the backlog (refresh if need be), delete this sprint
 # Repeat for all extra next-gen sprints.

